DAY 17

JENKINS: MASTER & SLAVE

	• It is used to distribute the builds.
	• It reduces the load on Jenkins Server.
	• Communication b/w master & slave is ssh
	• We need to install java
	• Slave can use any platform
	• Label = way of assigning work for slave.


Master and slave is used in a real time production environment. We don't run builds on the master node because it will crash. Instead we use slaves (worker nodes) to distribute the workload.

	• Master: handles the UI, stores configuration and schedules builds.
	• Slave: execute the actual build tasks assigned by the ma

	
STEPS

	1. Create slave instance and install java 11
amazon-linux-extras install java-openjdk11 -y
	2. SET UP THE SLAVE SERVER.
Dashboard -> Manage Jenkins -> Nodes & clouds -> New node -> node name: slave1 abc -> permanent agent -> Create
	3. Set number of executors = 3
Remote root directory: /tmp
Labels: slave1
Usage: select last option (expression matching...)
Launch method: select last option (via SSH)
Host: Paste the private IP of slave1 instance
Credentials: click on add > Jenkins
		○ Kind: Select SSH username with private key
		○ Description: slave1
		○ Username: ec2-user
		○ Private key: Select enter directly > Add
Paste the private key
Click Add
Go back to credentials > Select ec2-user
Host key verifying strategy -> last option (non)
Save
	4. To BUILD ON SLAVE
select Configure > check restrict where this Project can be run > Add slave1 label > Save

